    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "In-scope domain: FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at VAD operating conditions",
      "description": "Applicability is restricted to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry operating within the VAD flow regime: volumetric flow rates of 3–6 L/min, rotational speeds of 2000–3500 RPM, and blood analogue fluid properties (viscosity 3.5 cP, density 1060 kg/m³). The hemolysis model (power-law Giersiepen–Wurzinger correlation) is valid only for shear-exposure times below 700 ms and shear stresses below 400 Pa. Extrapolation outside these bounds is explicitly excluded from the assurance claim."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "VAD operating envelope: flow 3–6 L/min, speed 2000–3500 RPM",
      "description": "Concrete operating bounds: volumetric flow rate Q ∈ [3.0, 6.0] L/min; pump rotational speed N ∈ [2000, 3500] RPM; inlet total pressure 5–15 mmHg; outlet static pressure 80–120 mmHg; fluid temperature 37 ± 1 °C; haematocrit 40 ± 5%. Five design-point combinations (Q=3/N=3500, Q=4/N=3000, Q=5/N=2500, Q=5/N=3000, Q=6/N=2500) define the validated operating space. Transient start-up and cavitation regimes are explicitly excluded."
    }
  },
